SIMPLE: immortalize
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Immortalize
<hw>Im*mor"tal*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Immortalized</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Immortalizing</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>immortaliser</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To render immortal; to cause to live or exist
forever.</def> <rj><au>S. Clarke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To exempt from oblivion; to perpetuate in
fame.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Alexander had no Homer to <qex>immortalize</qex> his guilty
name.</q> <rj><qau>T. Dawes.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Immortalize</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Immortalize
<hw>Im*mor"tal*ize</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To become immortal.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Immortally</ent>⟦br⟧
